    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan for the PulseBoard channel plugin:\n\n## Summary\n\nAfter thorough exploration of `extensions/irc/`, `extensions/nostr/`, `extensions/telegram/`, `src/plugin-sdk/core.ts`, `src/plugin-sdk/runtime-store.ts`, and the channel adapter types, here's what the plan covers:\n\n### 7 New Files in `extensions/pulseboard/`\n\n| File | What it does |\n|------|-------------|\n| `package.json` | `@openclaw/pulseboard`, `\"module\"`, full `openclaw` block with channel metadata |\n| `openclaw.plugin.json` | `id: \"pulseboard\"`, `channels: [\"pulseboard\"]`, empty configSchema |\n| `src/types.ts` | `PulseBoardAccount`, `PulseBoardConfig`, `PulseBoardMessage` interfaces |\n| `src/runtime.ts` | `createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>` → exports `get/setPulseBoardRuntime` |\n| `src/channel.ts` | `createChatChannelPlugin` with stubs for config, setup, gateway, messaging + flat outbound adapter |\n| `index.ts` | `defineChannelPluginEntry` with `as ChannelPlugin` cast (IRC pattern) |\n| `setup-entry.ts` | `defineSetupPluginEntry(pulseBoardPlugin)` (Nostr/IRC pattern) |\n\n### One Important Design Note\n\n`getChatChannelMeta(id)` requires the channel to be in the core registry (`CHAT_CHANNEL_ORDER`). Since \"pulseboard\" is fictional and not registered, calling it would throw at runtime. The plan imports `getChatChannelMeta` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core` per the requirement, but defines `meta` as an inline literal object with the specified label/docsPath/blurb — exactly as the Nostr plugin does. A brief code comment explains the reasoning.",
